                                            <div class="related_pic justify-content-center">
                                              <a class="imgdq" href="products/1-2-2-pneumatic-fiber-feeder_01.webp"><img src="products/1-2-2-pneumatic-fiber-feeder_01b.webp" alt="Pneumatic Fiber Feeder"></a>
                                              <a href="products/1-2-2-pneumatic-fiber-feeder_02.webp"><img src="products/1-2-2-pneumatic-fiber-feeder_02b.webp" alt="Pneumatic Fiber Feeder"></a>
                                            </div>
                                          </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-md-6">
                                        <p>
                                            Pneumatic fiber feeder, as nonwoven machinery in the production of nonwoven fabrics, primarily utilizes airflow and pressure changes to control the density of fiber bundles, resulting in excellent uniformity and consistent density of the fiber batt. 
                                        </p>
                                        <div class="spec_list spec_list2">
                                            <dl><b>Working width:</b> 1400mm, 1700mm, 1850mm, 2150mm, 2350mm</dl>
                                            <dl><b>Capacity:</b> 200-600kg/h</dl>
                                          </div>
                                        <div class="request_btn request_btn1" onclick="openwindow('');return false">
                                          <notrans><span>Request Information</span></notrans>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="page_title">Functions</div>
                                <p>
                                    The pneumatic fiber feeder is used for the storage of fibers and fiber batts, and it utilizes airflow and pressure changes to control the density of fiber bundles, providing a quantitative supply to the next process.
                                </p>
                                <div class="page_title">Features</div>
                                <ul class="proitem">
                                   <li>PLC control ensures precise feeding, while the coordination with a variable frequency fan enables continuous fiber feeding.</li>
                                   <li>Both the longitudinal and cross directions of the fiber batt are adjustable, ensuring excellent uniform output. </li>
                                   <li>The fiber feeder comes with simple operation and digital control of fiber batt thickness.</li>
                                   <li>Compact and enclosed structure is designed to prevent oil leakage.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </content>
