                              <h2 itemprop="name" class="small_h2_font">Single Cylinder Carding Machine</h2>
                              <div class="pro_name">Carding system for converting fiber batt into fiber web</div>
                                <div class="row">
                                    <div class="col-md-6 order-md-last">
                                        <figure>
                                            <div class="left_pro_img">
                                              <div class="left_pics">
                                                <a href="products/1-2-3-single-cylinder-carding-machine_01.webp"><img itemprop="image" src="products/1-2-3-single-cylinder-carding-machine_01.webp" alt="Single Cylinder Carding Machine"></a>
                                              </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="related_pic justify-content-center">
                                              <a class="imgdq" href="products/1-2-3-single-cylinder-carding-machine_01.webp"><img src="products/1-2-3-single-cylinder-carding-machine_01b.webp" alt="Single Cylinder Carding Machine"></a>
                                              <a href="products/1-2-3-single-cylinder-carding-machine_02.webp"><img src="products/1-2-3-single-cylinder-carding-machine_02b.webp" alt="Single Cylinder Carding Machine"></a>
                                              <a href="products/1-2-3-single-cylinder-carding-machine_03.webp"><img src="products/1-2-3-single-cylinder-carding-machine_03b.webp" alt="Single Cylinder Carding Machine"></a>
                                            </div>
                                          </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-md-6">
                                        <p>
                                            In the nonwoven manufacturing process, the single cylinder carding machine plays a crucial role in transforming the fiber batt into fiber web. The fiber raw material undergoes processing in the carding machine, gradually breaking down from a clustered state into individual fibers, which are separated in different carding zones on the machine. Ultimately, these individual fibers are collected to form a complete fiber web, which is then used for further processing and manufacturing of nonwoven fabric products.
                                        </p>
                                       
                                        <div class="request_btn request_btn1" onClick="openwindow('');return false">
                                          <notrans><span>Request Information</span></notrans>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
