                                                <a href="products/1-2-4-double-cylinder-carding-machine_01.webp"><img itemprop="image" src="products/1-2-4-double-cylinder-carding-machine_01.webp" alt="Double Cylinder Carding Machine"></a>
                                              </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="related_pic justify-content-center">
                                              <a class="imgdq" href="products/1-2-4-double-cylinder-carding-machine_01.webp"><img src="products/1-2-4-double-cylinder-carding-machine_01b.webp" alt="Double Cylinder Carding Machine"></a>
                                              <a href="products/1-2-4-double-cylinder-carding-machine_02.webp"><img src="products/1-2-4-double-cylinder-carding-machine_02b.webp" alt="Double Cylinder Carding Machine"></a>
                                            </div>
                                          </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-md-6">
                                        <p>
                                            In the nonwoven manufacturing process, double cylinder carding machine is used to convert fiber raw materials into a fiber web. Fiber mass is progressively carded into individual fibers through various carding sections on the carding machine, and then collected to form a fiber web. Double cylinder carding machines performs exceptionally well in carding low denier and ultra-fine fibers.
                                        </p>
                                        <div class="request_btn request_btn1" onclick="openwindow('');return false">
                                          <notrans><span>Request Information</span></notrans>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                               <div class="page_title">Specifications</div>
                               <div class="table-responsive">
                                <table class="table text-center"> <tr > <td   > Working width </td> <td   > 1550mm </td> <td   > 1850mm </td> <td   > 2000mm </td> <td   > 2300mm </td> <td   > 2500mm </td> </tr> <tr > <td  rowspan="2"  > Diameter of cylinder </td> <td  colspan="5"  > Chest cylinder: 850mm </td> </tr> <tr > <td  colspan="5"  > Main cylinder: 1230mm </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Diameter of doffer </td> <td  colspan="5"  > 492mm </td> </tr> <tr > <td  rowspan="2"  > Output speed </td> <td  colspan="5"  > Ordinary: ≤50m/min </td> </tr> <tr > <td  colspan="5"  > High Speed: 60-80m/min </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Capacity </td> <td  colspan="5"  > 200-600kg/h (varying with fiber specification) </td> </tr> </table>
                               </div>
                               <div class="page_title">Functions</div>
                               <ul class="proitem">
                               <li>Double cylinder carding machine is applicable to various nonwoven production processes, like needle punching, thermal bonding, chemical bonding, etc.</li>
                               <li>The carding system can process a variety of fibers, such as polyester fibers, viscose fibers, nylon fibers, polypropylene fibers, jute fibers, glass fibers, carbon fibers, etc.</li>
                              </ul>
                                <div class="page_title">Features</div>
                                <ul class="proitem">
                                   <li>Double cylinder carding machine consists of a chest roller, main roller, double doffer, four random rollers.</li>
                                   <li>The carding machine is equipped with variable frequency control for speed adjustment, making it suitable for carding various fibers and producing different products.</li>
                                   <li>Exquisite mechanical craftsmanship limits the radial runout to within 0.02 mm, resulting in higher uniformity of the fiber web.</li>
                                   <li>The circulating suction device and enclosed housing help in reducing noise and fiber flocks.</li>
                                </ul>
