                                    <div class="col-md-6">
                                        <p>
                                            High speed cross lapper is an important nonwoven machinery used in various nonwoven manufacturing processes. This horizontal lapper features enhanced CV control and reduced GSM variations, ideal for high-capacity production and production of high-quality products. 
                                        </p>
                                        <div class="table-responsive">
                                            <table class="table"> <tr > <td   > Input width </td> <td  colspan="2"  > ≤2700mm </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Output width </td> <td  colspan="2"  > 2500mm~7000mm </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Infeed speed </td> <td   > ≤60m/min </td> <td   > ≤80m/min </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > CV </td> <td   > ≤5% </td> <td   > ≤3% </td></tr> </table>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="request_btn request_btn1" onclick="openwindow('');return false">
                                          <notrans><span>Request Information</span></notrans>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="page_title">Application</div>
                                <p>
                                    High speed cross lapper is used in different nonwoven manufacturing processes such as needle punching, thermal bonding, chemical bonding, and spunlace.
                                </p>
                                <div class="page_title">Features</div>
                                <ul class="proitem">
                                    <li>This horizontal lapper utilizes high-precision transmission devices controlled by servo motors and PLC.</li>
                                    <li>Variable speed and instantaneous speed control ensures excellent product uniformity.</li>
                                    <li>Dual-belt clamping conveyor is equipped with anti-static and lightweight apron.</li>
                                    <li>Enclosed design reduces the impact of air turbulence on the fiber web.</li>
                                    <li>Reciprocating rollers are made of carbon fiber and dynamically balanced for smoother motion.</li>
                                    <li>The profile auxiliary correction system further enhances the CV control.</li>
                                </ul>
