                              <h2 itemprop="name" class="small_h2_font">Web Drafter</h2>
                              <div class="pro_name">Drafting machine in nonwoven line for adjusting product properties, appearance and weight</div>
                                <div class="row">
                                    <div class="col-md-6 order-md-last">
                                        <figure>
                                            <div class="left_pro_img">
                                              <div class="left_pics">
                                                <a href="products/1-3-5-web-drafter_01.webp"><img itemprop="image" src="products/1-3-5-web-drafter_01.webp" alt="Web Drafter"></a>
                                              </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="related_pic justify-content-center">
                                              <a class="imgdq" href="products/1-3-5-web-drafter_01.webp"><img src="products/1-3-5-web-drafter_01b.webp" alt="Web Drafter"></a>
                                              <a href="products/1-3-5-web-drafter_02.webp"><img src="products/1-3-5-web-drafter_02b.webp" alt="Web Drafter"></a>
                                              <a href="products/1-3-5-web-drafter_03.webp"><img src="products/1-3-5-web-drafter_03b.webp" alt="Web Drafter"></a>
                                            </div>
                                          </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-md-6">
                                        <p>
                                          Web drafter is used to adjust the longitudinal distribution and orientation of the fiber web to improve the ratio of longitudinal and lateral strength to be similar, and it can also adjust the thickness and density of the fiber web to enhance production yield in conjunction with a nonwoven production line.
                                        </p>
                                        <div class="table-responsive">
                                            <table class="table"> <tr >  <td   > Number of roller </td> <td   > 5 roller </td> <td   > 9 roller </td> <td   > 15 roller </td> <td   > 21 roller </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Working width </td> <td  colspan="4"  > 2000mm~7000mm </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Linear speed </td> <td  colspan="4"  > ≤40m/min </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Drafting Ratio </td> <td  colspan="4"  > 1:1~1:3 </td> </tr> </table>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="request_btn request_btn1" onclick="openwindow('');return false">
                                          <notrans><span>Request Information</span></notrans>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="page_title">Application</div>
                                <p>
                                    Web drafter is suitable for various nonwoven manufacturing processes, such as needle punching, thermal bonding, and spunlace.
                                </p>
                                <div class="page_title">Features</div>
                                <ul class="proitem">
                                    <li>Web drafter adopts independent servo control or inverter control, which is customizable according to demand.</li>
                                    <li>Each drafting roller group is independently driven, allowing for individual adjustment of drafting ratios.</li>
                                    <li>Anti-static belts with embossed textures and guiding devices are equipped.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </content>
