                                    <div class="col-md-6">
                                        <p>
                                            The feeding machine, also known as a CBF feeder, is an essential nonwoven equipment used in conjunction with a needle punching machine during nonwoven production. Its primary function is to ensure that the loose fiber web enters the needling zone of the needle punching machine smoothly, thereby preventing the fiber web from being excessively stretched or slid.
                                        </p>
                                        <div class="table-responsive">
                                            <table class="table"> <tr ><td   > Production width </td> <td   > 2000mm-9000mm </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Feeding speed </td> <td   > ≤10m/min </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Available fiber web </td> <td   > ≤4000gsm </td> </tr> </table>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="request_btn request_btn1" onclick="openwindow('');return false">
                                          <notrans><span>Request Information</span></notrans>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="page_title">Functions</div>
                                <p class="mb-0">Feeding machine smoothly feeds the loose fiber web into the needling zone of the needle punching machine, playing a crucial role in nonwoven manufacturing processes.</p>
                                <div class="page_title">Features</div>
                                <ul class="proitem">
                                   <li>Feeding machine features variable frequency speed control for feeding.</li>
                                   <li>The movable base facilitates cleaning and maintenance.</li>
                                   <li>Adjustable clamping conveyor is suitable for the production of high GSM products.</li>
                                </ul>
