                                    <div class="col-md-6">
                                        <p>
                                            Double board needle punching machine is crucial nonwoven equipment, distinguished by its two needle boards (or needling zones), which provide cost-effectiveness and process optimization advantages. By combining different stroke types, the double board needleloom can meet various production process requirements.
                                        </p>
                                        <div class="spec_list spec_list2">
                                            <dl><b>Needling frequency:</b> ≤600 rpm, ≤1200 rpm</dl>
                                            <dl><b>Working width:</b> 2000mm~9000mm</dl>
                                          </div>
                                        <div class="request_btn request_btn1" onclick="openwindow('');return false">
                                          <notrans><span>Request Information</span></notrans>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="page_title">Applications</div>
                                <p>
                                    Double board needle punching machine is utilized in the primary production processes of various nonwoven products, including but not limited to carpets, felts, linings, geotextiles, filtration media, oilcloth base fabrics, shoe midsoles, synthetic leather substrates, and more.
                                </p>
                                <div class="page_title">Specifications</div>
                                <div class="table-responsive">
                                    <table class="table text-center"> <tr ><td   > Needling frequency </td> <td  colspan="2"  > ≤600 rpm </td> <td  colspan="2"  > ≤1200 rpm </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Working width </td> <td  colspan="4"  > 2000mm~9000mm </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Stroke range </td> <td  colspan="4"  > 20~60mm </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Stroke type </td> <td   > Double Up-stroke </td> <td  colspan="2"  >Double Down-stroke</td> <td   > Tandem Up & Down </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Needling zone </td> <td  colspan="4"  > (▼▼) ; (▲▲) ; (▼▲) </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Needle density </td> <td  colspan="4"  > ≤7500n/m x2 Needle Board </td></tr> </table>
                                </div>


                                <div class="page_title">Features</div>
                                <ul class="proitem">
                                    <li>Automatic variable frequency control.</li>
                                    <li>Advanced segmented modular design offers high structural strength, ensuring stable and reliable operation.</li>
                                    <li>Computer-controlled random needle distribution results in superior appearance and quality of products.</li>
                                    <li>Double board needleloom features dual crank shaft structure and dual tandem drive.</li>
                                </ul>
