                                    <div class="col-md-6">
                                        <p>
                                          Heating calender machine is primarily used for thermal treatment of nonwoven products. By applying a certain temperature and pressure, it can alter the thickness, appearance, and certain properties of nonwoven fabric products.
                                        </p>
                                        <div class="spec_list spec_list2">
                                            <dl><b>Category:</b> Two rollers, Three rollers</dl>
                                            <dl><b>Working width:</b> 2000mm~7000mm</dl>
                                            <dl><b>Linear speed:</b> 1~25m/min</dl>
                                          </div>
                                        <div class="request_btn request_btn1" onclick="openwindow('');return false">
                                          <notrans><span>Request Information</span></notrans>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="page_title">Applications</div>
                                <p>
                                    Heating calender machine is an integral part of the thermal bonding production process and is used to directly produce low GSM nonwoven products such as garment linings, composite substrates, and filtering materials, etc.
                                </p>
                                <div class="page_title">Specifications</div>
                                <div class="table-responsive">
                                    <table class="table text-center"> <tr > <td   > Category </td> <td   > Two rollers </td> <td   > Three rollers </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Working width </td> <td  colspan="2"  > 2000mm~7000mm </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Linear speed </td> <td  colspan="2"  > 1~25m/min </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Surface temperature </td> <td  colspan="2"  > ≤230℃ </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Temperature variation </td> <td  colspan="2"  > ≤+/-2℃ </td> </tr> <tr > <td  rowspan="2"  > Heating method </td> <td  colspan="2"  > Hermetic thermal oil (Electrical heating) </td> </tr> <tr > <td  colspan="2"  > External thermal oil </td> </tr> </table>
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="page_title">Features</div>
                                <ul class="proitem">
                                   <li>Variable frequency control enables adjustable speed.</li>
                                   <li>Each heating roller can be independently adjusted for heating, with precise automatic temperature control.</li>
                                   <li>With high precision and hardness roller surface, rollers are heat-treated for durability and deformation resistance.</li>
                                   <li>Hermetic thermal oil or separate circulating thermal oil system can adapt to different types of production.</li>
                                   <li>Overload protection, protective cover, emergency stop, and other multiple safety protections are equipped.</li>
