                                            </div>
                                            <div class="related_pic justify-content-center">
                                              <a class="imgdq" href="products/2-1-6-shoe-fabric-production-line_01.webp"><img src="products/2-1-6-shoe-fabric-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Shoe Material Production Line"></a>
                                              <a href="products/2-1-6-shoe-fabric-production-line_02.webp"><img src="products/2-1-6-shoe-fabric-production-line_02b.webp" alt="Shoe Material Production Line"></a>
                                            </div>
                                          </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-md-6">
                                        <p>
                                          Shoe material production line processes various fiber raw materials through opening, blending, carding, web forming, needle punching, and thermal calendaring processes to produce rolls of fabric. Subsequently, the nonwoven rolls can undergo further processing or additional chemical bonding treatments.
                                        </p> 
                                        
                                        <div class="request_btn request_btn1" onclick="openwindow('');return false">
                                          <notrans><span>Request Information</span></notrans>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
