                                <div class="etw_gallery etw_gallery4">
                                    <figure>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li><a href="products/2-1-6-shoe-fabric-production-line_03.webp"><img src="products/2-1-6-shoe-fabric-production-line_03b.webp" alt="Various shoe materials"></a><span>Various shoe materials</span></li>
                                            <li><a href="products/2-1-6-shoe-fabric-production-line_04.webp"><img src="products/2-1-6-shoe-fabric-production-line_04b.webp" alt="Insole board substrate"></a><span>Insole board substrate</span></li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </figure>
                                </div>
                                <div class="page_title">Application</div>
                                        <p>
                                          It utilizes needle punching technology as primarily process to produce insole board substrate and shoes lining.  <br>
                                          The nonwoven felt made by this line subsequently will be used as substrate or base material for making insole board, toe puff, shoes lining, etc. 
                                        </p>
                                
                                <div class="page_title">Features</div>
                                <ul class="proitem">
                                    <li>Shoe material production line adopts relatively high-end configurations to meet product requirements for appearance, texture, uniformity, strength, and other performance aspects.</li>
                                    <li>Recommended configurations include multiple opening and blending processes, double cylinder carding machines, and high-speed needle punching to meet the production demands for high-quality products.</li>
                                </ul>
