                                <h2 itemprop="name" class="small_h2_font">Thermal Bonded Padding Production Line</h2>
                                <div class="pro_name">Nonwoven Thermal Bonding Production Line</div>
                                <div class="row">
                                    <div class="col-md-6 order-md-last">
                                        <figure>
                                            <div class="left_pro_img">
                                              <div class="left_pics">
                                                <a href="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_01.webp"><img itemprop="image" src="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_01.webp" alt="Thermal Bonded Padding Production Line"></a>
                                              </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="related_pic justify-content-center">
                                              <a class="imgdq" href="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_01.webp"><img src="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Thermal Bonded Padding Production Line"></a>
                                              <a href="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_02.webp"><img src="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_02b.webp" alt="Thermal Bonded Padding Production Line"></a>
                                              <a href="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_03.webp"><img src="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_03b.webp" alt="Thermal Bonded Padding Production Line"></a>
                                              <a href="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_04.webp"><img src="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_04b.webp" alt="Thermal Bonded Padding Production Line"></a>
                                              <a href="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_05.webp"><img src="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_05b.webp" alt="Thermal Bonded Padding Production Line"></a>
                                            </div>
                                          </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-md-6">
                                        <p>
                                            Thermal bonded padding production line primarily utilizes hot air consolidation, also known as thermal bonding technology, to manufacture nonwoven materials with a high-density three-dimensional network structure, commonly referred to as padding.</p><p>Polyester fibers and hot melt fibers (low melting point fibers) are processed through opening, blending, carding, web forming, thermal bonding & drying processes to produce rigid sheets. Different fiber combinations and process adjustments can be chosen according to various market demands to produce products with different textures, hardness, weight, and thickness.
                                            </p>
                                        
                                        <div class="request_btn request_btn1" onclick="openwindow('');return false">
                                          <notrans><span>Request Information</span></notrans>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="page_title">Application</div>
                                <p>The produced materials are used as fillings for sofas, mattresses, and other products, as well as some thermal insulation materials. Products formed with the involvement of a vertical lapper have a more vertically aligned fiber arrangement inside, providing better resilience and structural stability on the product surface. Padding with this feature is particularly suitable for high-end mattresses and cushions.</p>
                                
                                <div class="page_title">End Products</div>
                                <div class="etw_gallery etw_gallery4">
                                    <figure>
                                        <ul>
                                            <li><a href="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_06.webp"><img src="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_06b.webp" alt="Filter Media"></a> <span>Filter Media</span></li>
                                            <li><a href="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_07.webp"><img src="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_07b.webp" alt="Insulation Felt"></a> <span>Insulation Felt</span></li>
                                            <li><a href="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_08.webp"><img src="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_08b.webp" alt="Padding"></a> <span>Padding</span></li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </figure>
                                </div>
                                <div class="page_title">Features</div>
                                <p>The thermal bonded padding production line configuration is flexibly adapted to different products and automation requirements. It mainly includes fiber opening and blending equipment, carding machines, web formation machines, web bonding and drying equipment, calendering and ironing equipment, slitting & winding machines, etc., to meet production needs, offering a diverse range of product specifications. </p>
                                <div class="page_title">Specifications </div>
                              
                                <div class="table-responsive">
                                  <table class="table"> <tr > <td width="50%" > Production width </td> <td   > 2000mm - 3200mm </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Product weight </td> <td   > 100gsm ~5000gsm </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Design capacity </td> <td   > 200-400kg/h </td> </tr> <tr > <td   > Raw material </td> <td   > PET, PP, Low Melt fiber / Bio-component fiber </td>  </tr> </table>
                              </div>
