                                <h2 itemprop="name" class="small_h2_font">Scouring Pad Production Line</h2>
                                <div class="pro_name">Nonwoven Chemical Bonding & Needle Punching Combo Production Line</div>
                                <div class="row">
                                    <div class="col-md-6 order-md-last">
                                        <figure>
                                            <div class="left_pro_img">
                                              <div class="left_pics">
                                                <a href="products/2-3-2-scouring-pad-production-line_01.webp"><img itemprop="image" src="products/2-3-2-scouring-pad-production-line_01.webp" alt="Scouring Pad Production Line"></a>
                                              </div>
                                            </div>
                                          </figure>
                                          <div class="request_btn" onclick="openwindow('');return false">
                                            <notrans><span>Request Information</span></notrans>
                                          </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-md-6">
                                        <p>
                                            Scouring pad production line utilizes a combination of chemical bonding and hot air drying processes to produce cleaning cloth products.
                                        </p>
                                        <p>Synthetic fiber raw materials undergo processes including opening, blending, carding, web forming, needle punching, spraying, drying and shaping, and winding to produce rolls of fabric. Subsequent secondary processing can involve impregnation bonding or spray bonding, followed by drying and shaping to produce the final product. 
                                        </p>
                                        <p>Chemical bonding production lines can apply different fiber ratios and processes according to different market demands to produce products with different weights, thicknesses, and uses.
                                        </p>
                                       
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="row">
                                  <div class="col-12">
                                    <div class="page_title">Application</div>
                                    <p>Conventional chemical bonding lines are used for producing kitchen and bathroom cleaning cloths, and with special processes, they can also be used to produce abrasive materials.</p>
                                  </div>
                                </div>
                                
                                
                                
                                <div class="page_title">End Products</div>
                                <div class="etw_gallery etw_gallery4">
                                    <figure>
                                        <ul>
