                                              </div>
                                            </div>
                                          </figure>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-md-6">
                                        <p>Chemical steeping and bonding production line processes synthetic fiber raw materials through opening, blending, carding, web forming, further carding, saturation impregnation, drying and shaping, and winding to produce rolls of fabric. </p>
                                        <p>Different fiber ratios and processes can be selected according to various market demands to produce products with different weights and applications.  </p><p>
                                          Synthetic fibers are predominantly used as raw materials, resulting in lighter weight and lower density products primarily used for linings in clothing. They can also be utilized as substrates for further processing or lamination.</p>
                                        <div class="request_btn request_btn1" onclick="openwindow('');return false">
                                          <notrans><span>Request Information</span></notrans>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="page_title">Application</div>
                                <p>Chemical steeping and bonding production line primarily adopts chemically impregnating and bonding to reinforce fiber webs, typically employed in the production of nonwoven linings and substrates.</p>
                                
                                <div class="page_title">End Products</div>
                                <div class="etw_gallery etw_gallery4">
