                      <notrans>
                            
                        <div class="content">
                            <div class="hub_production_line">
                                <div class="hub_title_big"><a href="2-1-needle-punching-line.html">Needle Punching Line</a></div>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                      <div class="pro_img">
                                        <a href="2-1-1-nonwoven-carpet-production-line.html"><img src="products/2-1-1-nonwoven-carpet-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Nonwoven Carpet Production Line"></a>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="pro_des">
                                        <a href="2-1-1-nonwoven-carpet-production-line.html">Nonwoven Carpet Production Line</a>
                                        <p>Typically, polyester staple fiber is used as the main raw material for producing nonwoven carpets. The process involves fiber opening, blending, carding, web forming, and needle punching to form the base fabric. Then, various treatments such as velour, jacquard, or striped patterns can be applied, followed by bonding to create nonwoven carpets with different styles or surface patterns.</p>
                                        <a href="2-1-1-nonwoven-carpet-production-line.html" class="learn_more">Learn More</a>
                                      </div>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                      <div class="pro_img">
                                        <a href="2-1-2-geotextile-production-line.html"><img src="products/2-1-2-geotextile-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Geotextile Production Line"></a>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="pro_des">
                                        <a href="2-1-2-geotextile-production-line.html">Geotextile Production Line</a>
                                        <p>Geotextile production line primarily utilizes needle-punching nonwoven technology to produce geotextile products of different materials, widths, and GSMs. <br>
                                            Typically, polyester or polypropylene staple fibers are used as the main raw materials, which undergo processes such as fiber opening, blending, carding, web forming, needle punching reinforcement, and thermal bonding to produce geotextile rolls. </p>
                                            <a href="2-1-2-geotextile-production-line.html" class="learn_more">Learn More</a>
                                      </div>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                      <div class="pro_img">
                                        <a href="2-1-3-filter-felt-production-line.html"><img src="products/2-1-3-filter-felt-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Filter Felt Production Line"></a>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="pro_des">
                                        <a href="2-1-3-filter-felt-production-line.html">Filter Felt Production Line</a>
                                        <p>Filter felt production line processes various fiber raw materials through opening, blending, carding, web forming, needle punching, and thermal calendaring processes to produce rolls of fabric. Subsequently, further processing or composite treatments are applied to obtain a more diverse range of filtering material products.</p>
                                        <a href="2-1-3-filter-felt-production-line.html" class="learn_more">Learn More</a>
                                      </div>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                      <div class="pro_img">
                                        <a href="2-1-4-automotive-interior-felt-production-line.html"><img src="products/2-1-4-automotive-interior-felt-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Automotive Interior Felt Production Line"></a>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="pro_des">
                                        <a href="2-1-4-automotive-interior-felt-production-line.html">Automotive Interior Felt Production Line</a>
                                        <p>Automotive interior felt production line processes various fiber raw materials through opening, blending, carding, web forming, needle punching, and thermal calendaring processes to produce rolls of fabric. Subsequently, further processing or composite treatments are applied to obtain a more diverse range of functional materials.</p>
                                        <a href="2-1-4-automotive-interior-felt-production-line.html" class="learn_more">Learn More</a>
                                      </div>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                      <div class="pro_img">
                                        <a href="2-1-5-synthetic-leather-substrate-production-line.html"><img src="products/2-1-5-synthetic-leather-substrate-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Synthetic Leather Substrate Production Line"></a>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="pro_des">
                                        <a href="2-1-5-synthetic-leather-substrate-production-line.html">Synthetic Leather Substrate Production Line</a>
                                        <p>Synthetic leather substrate production line processes various fiber raw materials through opening, blending, carding, web forming, needle punching, and thermal calendaring processes to produce rolls of fabric. Subsequently, the nonwoven rolls undergo further processing and some modification treatments.</p>
                                        <a href="2-1-5-synthetic-leather-substrate-production-line.html" class="learn_more">Learn More</a>
                                      </div>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                      <div class="pro_img">
                                        <a href="2-1-6-shoe-fabric-production-line.html"><img src="products/2-1-6-shoe-fabric-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Shoe Material Production Line"></a>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="pro_des">
                                        <a href="2-1-6-shoe-fabric-production-line.html">Shoe Material Production Line</a>
                                        <p>Shoe material production line processes various fiber raw materials through opening, blending, carding, web forming, needle punching, and thermal calendaring processes to produce rolls of fabric. Subsequently, the nonwoven rolls can undergo further processing or additional chemical bonding treatments.</p>
                                        <a href="2-1-6-shoe-fabric-production-line.html" class="learn_more">Learn More</a>
                                      </div>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                      <div class="pro_img">
                                        <a href="2-1-7-nonwoven-felt-production-line.html"><img src="products/2-1-7-nonwoven-felt-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Nonwoven Felt Production Line"></a>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="pro_des">
                                        <a href="2-1-7-nonwoven-felt-production-line.html">Nonwoven Felt Production Line</a>
                                        <p>Nonwoven felt production line processes various fiber raw materials through opening, blending, carding, web forming, needle punching, and thermal calendaring processes to produce rolls of fabric. The selection of raw materials can be flexibly adjusted according to different market demands and applications, allowing for the production of products with different textures, materials, and styles.</p>
                                        <a href="2-1-7-nonwoven-felt-production-line.html" class="learn_more">Learn More</a>
                                      </div>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                      <div class="pro_img">
                                        <a href="2-1-8-cleaning-cloth-production-line.html"><img src="products/2-1-8-cleaning-cloth-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Cleaning Cloth Production Line"></a>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="pro_des">
                                        <a href="2-1-8-cleaning-cloth-production-line.html">Cleaning Cloth Production Line</a>
                                        <p>Cleaning cloth production line processes polyester fibers and absorbent fiber raw materials through opening, blending, carding, web forming, needle punching, and thermal calendaring processes to produce rolls of fabric. Depending on different market demands, various fiber ratios can be selected, and the process can be adjusted to produce cleaning cloth products with different textures, absorbencies, and durability.</p>
                                        <a href="2-1-8-cleaning-cloth-production-line.html" class="learn_more">Learn More</a>
                                      </div>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                      <div class="pro_img">
                                        <a href="2-1-9-acoustic-fiber-board-production-line.html"><img src="products/2-1-9-acoustic-fiber-board-production-line_02b.webp" alt="Nonwoven Acoustic Panel Production Line"></a>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="pro_des">
                                        <a href="2-1-9-acoustic-fiber-board-production-line.html">Nonwoven Acoustic Panel Production Line</a>
                                        <p>Acoustic fiber board production line processes polyester fibers and low-melting fibers through opening, blending, carding, web forming, needle punching, and thermal bonding to produce nonwoven sheets. Products of different GSMs, thicknesses, and densities can be produced by selecting different fiber ratios and adjusting the process according to different market demands.</p>
                                        <a href="2-1-9-acoustic-fiber-board-production-line.html" class="learn_more">Learn More</a>
                                      </div>
                                    </li>
                                  </ul>
                            </div>
                            <div class="hub_production_line">
                                <div class="hub_title_big"><a href="2-2-thermobonding-line.html">Thermobonding Line</a></div>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                      <div class="pro_img">
                                        <a href="2-2-1-thermal-bonded-wadding-production-line.html"><img src="products/2-2-1-thermal-bonded-wadding-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Thermal Bonded Wadding Production Line"></a>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="pro_des">
                                        <a href="2-2-1-thermal-bonded-wadding-production-line.html">Thermal Bonded Wadding Production Line</a>
                                        <p>Thermal bonded wadding production line processes polyester fibers and low melt fibers through opening, blending, carding, web forming, web bonding, and drying processes to produce lofty rolls. Different fiber combinations and process adjustments can be chosen according to various market demands to produce products with different textures, thicknesses, and loftiness.
                                        </p>
                                        <a href="2-2-1-thermal-bonded-wadding-production-line.html" class="learn_more">Learn More</a>
                                      </div>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                      <div class="pro_img">
                                        <a href="2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line.html"><img src="products/2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Thermal Bonded Padding Production Line"></a>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="pro_des">
                                        <a href="2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line.html">Thermal Bonded Padding Production Line</a>
                                        <p>Thermal bonded padding production line primarily utilizes hot air consolidation, also known as thermal bonding technology, to manufacture nonwoven materials with a high-density three-dimensional network structure, commonly referred to as padding.</p>
                                        <a href="2-2-2-thermal-bonded-padding-production-line.html" class="learn_more">Learn More</a>
                                      </div>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                      <div class="pro_img">
                                        <a href="2-2-3-automotive-soundproofing-felt-production-line.html"><img src="products/2-2-3-automotive-soundproofing-felt-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Automotive Insulation Felt Production Line"></a>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="pro_des">
                                        <a href="2-2-3-automotive-soundproofing-felt-production-line.html">Automotive Insulation Felt Production Line</a>
                                        <p>Automotive insulation felt production line primarily utilizes hot air consolidation to manufacture nonwoven materials with a high-density three-dimensional network structure. The product made by airlaid web formation possesses better 3D fiber orientation, enhancing the thermal insulation properties.</p>
                                        <a href="2-2-3-automotive-soundproofing-felt-production-line.html" class="learn_more">Learn More</a>
                                      </div>
                                    </li>
                                  </ul>
                            </div>
                            <div class="hub_production_line">
                                <div class="hub_title_big"><a href="2-3-chemical-bonding-line.html">Chemical Bonding Line</a></div>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                      <div class="pro_img">
                                        <a href="2-3-1-spray-bonded-wadding-production-line.html"><img src="products/2-3-1-spray-bonded-wadding-production-line_01b.webp" alt="Spray Bonded Wadding Production Line"></a>
                                      </div>
                                      <div class="pro_des">
                                        <a href="2-3-1-spray-bonded-wadding-production-line.html">Spray Bonded Wadding Production Line</a>
                                        <p>Chemical bonding technology is primarily employed to produce nonwoven materials with a three-dimensional network structure, characterized by fluffy texture.</p>
                                        <a href="2-3-1-spray-bonded-wadding-production-line.html" class="learn_more">Learn More</a>
