                      </div>
                      <div id="collapse1" class="collapse show" aria-labelledby="heading1" data-parent="#accordionExample" itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                        <div class="card-body" itemprop="text">
                          <p>Nonwoven fabric is a flat and porous sheet or roll made from single fibers, melted plastic, or plastic films. As the name suggests, it is not produced through traditional textile processes.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card">
                      <div class="card-header" id="heading2">
                        <h3 class="my-0">
                          <span class="btn btn-link btn-block text-left collapsed" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapse2" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapse2">
                            <div class="accordion-item-icon">
                              <div class="accordion-item-icon-open"><i class="icon-plus"></i></div>
                              <div class="accordion-item-icon-close"><i class="icon-minus"></i></div>
                            </div>
                            <div itemprop="name">What is nonwoven manufacturing?</div>
                          </span>
                        </h3>
                      </div>
                      <div id="collapse2" class="collapse show" aria-labelledby="heading2" data-parent="#accordionExample" itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer">
                        <div class="card-body" itemprop="text">
                          <p>Nonwoven fabric, also known as nonwoven textile, is made by bonding short fibers or filament fibers together through chemical, mechanical, thermal, or solvent processes to create sheets or rolls of material.</p>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card">
                      <div class="card-header" id="heading3">
                        <h3 class="my-0">
